translated: Jeansson, Johan Ragnar Ludvig, director, Kalmar, b. 16/7/99 in Kalmar, son of director Ragnar J. and Tyra Bruun. Married on 26 to Helga Sjöstedt. Children: Gunnel b. 27, Dagmar b. 35. - Approximately 5 years of studies in fat chemistry (margarine and oil industry) in Zurich, Cologne, Hamburg, Berlin, Vienna, and London. Technical manager and managing director for Margarin A-B Svea in Kalmar since 1925, director and board member of A-B Liva Fabr. in Kalmar. Member of the city council from 1939 to 1946, member of the finance committee from 1939 to 1942, member of the air-defense committee, board member of Skand. Bankens avd :kont. in Kalmar, Margarine-fabr. Försäljn. A-B in Stockholm, Bef:-utb:förb. överstyr, and Kalmar fo bef :utb :förb. o. local section, commander for Kalmar's home defense district. Member of SFMK, initiator:tag. for the formation of Kalmar FM'F. Deputy county governor and county association, Grand Master of the Central Association of Swedish Freemasonry, recipient of the Royal Swedish Central Sports Federation's commendation medal in gold.
